{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The conversation history passed to the LLM is trimmed to the most recent 10 messages when the full history exceeds the context window.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is local module handoff: history store/collector -> prompt builder -> LLM request payload. A pure unit test of a trim helper can miss wiring bugs (wrong order, wrong slice point, trim not applied before request assembly). Rejected higher levels: behavior text is only about trimming to 10 before send, with no requirement for real OS/network/subprocess or real model-quality judgment.","test_description":"Run the chat request path in-process with a fake LLM client that captures payload. Provide >10 prior messages and assert exactly the most recent 10 (correct order) are sent.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated response addresses the customer's question rather than producing a generic or off-topic reply.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM output quality (relevance/on-topicness). A stubbed model would always pass and hide real failures in model behavior or prompt steering. Rejected Workflow: behavior asks for one response quality check, not a multi-agentic pipeline outcome.","test_description":"Send representative customer questions to the real model path and evaluate response relevance (rubric or human/LLM judge with acceptance threshold) across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The tone re-check correctly identifies when a response is too formal for a casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The key failure is tone judgment correctness (\"correctly identifies ... too formal\"), which depends on real model/classifier behavior; mocks hide this. Regeneration trigger can be asserted in the same run after the real judgment. Rejected Workflow: although regeneration occurs, the behavior’s core acceptance is single judgment correctness plus trigger, not end-to-end quality across multiple agentic stages.","test_description":"Use casual-tier prompts likely to induce formal drafts, run real tone-check path, and assert formal drafts are flagged and a regeneration call is issued.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.14}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full exchange (user message, generated response, any regenerations) is persisted to the database with correct timestamps.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is persistence wiring/state integrity across chat service and DB repository. An in-process test with a real local DB (or transactional test DB) catches schema/transaction/order/timestamp mapping bugs. Rejected System: behavior does not require real external networked DB or OS-level primitives beyond local integration.","test_description":"Execute chat flow with a local test DB, force a regeneration case, then assert stored records include user message, initial draft, regeneration, and correct timestamp sequencing/fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary risk is orchestration/state handoff (response selection in delivery layer) across modules. This can be caught with deterministic trigger + two canned model outputs in-process. Rejected Agentic: behavior text conditions on trigger already happening (\"When the tone check triggers regeneration\"), so model judgment quality is not required to verify replacement semantics.","test_description":"Run end-to-end in-process request handling with tone-check forced true and two sequential model outputs; assert returned payload to customer is only the second response and first draft is absent from outward response.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
